{
  "resourceType": "Bundle",
  "id": "careplan-goal-model-bundle",
  "type": "transaction",
  "_comment": "FHIR R4 mirror using ONLY HL7-defined fields. Demonstrates the goal/objective/task distinction with real fields: Goal.description = the AIM ('well-controlled'); Goal.target = the OBJECTIVE (measure A1c + detailRange 6.5-7.5%); CarePlan.activity -> Task = the completable actions. No invented 'objective' record. Assumes Patient/Practitioners exist.",
  "entry": [
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:consent-ccm",
      "request": { "method": "PUT", "url": "Consent/CONSENT-CCM-1" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Consent",
        "id": "CONSENT-CCM-1",
        "_comment": "The CCM consent gate (a real FHIR resource, not invented).",
        "status": "active",
        "scope": { "coding": [ { "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/consentscope", "code": "treatment" } ] },
        "category": [ { "coding": [ { "system": "http://loinc.org", "code": "59284-0", "display": "Patient consent" } ] } ],
        "patient": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" },
        "dateTime": "2026-06-08"
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:enc-awv",
      "request": { "method": "PUT", "url": "Encounter/AWV-1" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Encounter",
        "id": "AWV-1",
        "_comment": "The AWV the plan was created in (CDA encompassingEncounter -> FHIR Encounter).",
        "status": "finished",
        "class": { "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/v3-ActCode", "code": "AMB", "display": "ambulatory" },
        "type": [ { "coding": [ { "system": "http://www.ama-assn.org/go/cpt", "code": "G0439", "display": "Annual wellness visit" } ] } ],
        "subject": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" },
        "period": { "start": "2026-06-08" }
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:cond-dm",
      "request": { "method": "PUT", "url": "Condition/PROB-1" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Condition",
        "id": "PROB-1",
        "clinicalStatus": { "coding": [ { "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/condition-clinical", "code": "active" } ] },
        "category": [ { "coding": [ { "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/condition-category", "code": "problem-list-item" } ] } ],
        "code": { "coding": [ { "system": "http://snomed.info/sct", "code": "44054006", "display": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus" } ] },
        "subject": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" }
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:goal-gm",
      "request": { "method": "PUT", "url": "Goal/GOAL-1" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Goal",
        "id": "GOAL-1",
        "_comment": "ONE Goal carries BOTH the aim and the objective using real fields. description = the AIM (well-controlled). target = the OBJECTIVE: measure (A1c) + detailRange (6.5-7.5%). There is no separate 'objective' resource. achievementStatus will carry nature's verdict (here sustaining/in-progress).",
        "lifecycleStatus": "active",
        "achievementStatus": { "coding": [ { "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/goal-achievement", "code": "in-progress", "display": "In Progress" } ] },
        "category": [ { "coding": [ { "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/goal-category", "code": "treatment" } ] } ],
        "description": { "coding": [ { "system": "http://snomed.info/sct", "code": "412776001", "display": "Well controlled" } ], "text": "Diabetes well-controlled" },
        "subject": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" },
        "_comment_expressedBy": "PATIENT'S STATEMENT ABOUT THE GOAL: expressedBy = Patient marks this as a patient-stated goal (the patient is the goal-EXPRESSER, a distinct role from performer). R4 element is Goal.expressedBy; RENAMED to Goal.source in R5. note carries the patient's own words.",
        "expressedBy": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" },
        "note": [ { "text": "Patient: \"I want to keep my diabetes under control so I can keep up with my grandkids.\"" } ],
        "addresses": [ { "reference": "Condition/PROB-1", "display": "Type 2 diabetes mellitus" } ],
        "target": [
          {
            "measure": { "coding": [ { "system": "http://loinc.org", "code": "4548-4", "display": "Hemoglobin A1c" } ] },
            "detailRange": {
              "low": { "value": 6.5, "unit": "%", "system": "http://unitsofmeasure.org", "code": "%" },
              "high": { "value": 7.5, "unit": "%", "system": "http://unitsofmeasure.org", "code": "%" }
            },
            "dueDate": "2026-12-08"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:task-rx",
      "request": { "method": "PUT", "url": "Task/T-RX" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Task", "id": "T-RX",
        "_comment": "TEAM task (provider). Completable. Task.status carries completion (team's accountability) - separate field from Goal.achievementStatus.",
        "status": "requested", "intent": "order",
        "code": { "coding": [ { "system": "http://snomed.info/sct", "code": "33633005", "display": "Prescription of drug" } ], "text": "Prescribe/adjust medication regimen" },
        "for": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" },
        "owner": { "reference": "Practitioner/DR-1" }
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:task-sch",
      "request": { "method": "PUT", "url": "Task/T-SCH" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Task", "id": "T-SCH",
        "_comment": "TEAM task (care manager). Scheduling appointments IS completable by the team.",
        "status": "requested", "intent": "order",
        "code": { "text": "Schedule four follow-up appointments" },
        "for": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" },
        "owner": { "reference": "Practitioner/CM-1" }
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:task-transport",
      "request": { "method": "PUT", "url": "Task/T-TRANSPORT" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Task", "id": "T-TRANSPORT",
        "_comment": "TEAM task (care manager, SDOH). Removing a barrier is completable; it cannot guarantee the patient travels.",
        "status": "requested", "intent": "order",
        "code": { "text": "Arrange transportation" },
        "for": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" },
        "owner": { "reference": "Practitioner/CM-1" }
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:task-attend",
      "request": { "method": "PUT", "url": "Task/T-ATTEND" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Task", "id": "T-ATTEND",
        "_comment": "PATIENT-expected task. owner = Patient (a real allowed Task.owner). It is an expectation, never a team deliverable - so the team cannot 'complete' it on the patient's behalf.",
        "status": "requested", "intent": "order",
        "code": { "text": "Attend the four scheduled appointments" },
        "for": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" },
        "owner": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" }
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:careplan",
      "request": { "method": "PUT", "url": "CarePlan/CarePlan-GM-0001" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "CarePlan",
        "id": "CarePlan-GM-0001",
        "_comment": "The plan ties it together with real fields: addresses -> Condition, goal -> Goal, activity.reference -> the Tasks. Goal linkage for referenced tasks rides at plan level (CarePlan.goal) - the known CDA/FHIR asymmetry.",
        "status": "active", "intent": "plan",
        "title": "Care Plan (Goal/Objective/Task model) - Jane Q. Patient",
        "subject": { "reference": "Patient/PT-12345" },
        "encounter": { "reference": "Encounter/AWV-1" },
        "addresses": [ { "reference": "Condition/PROB-1" } ],
        "goal": [ { "reference": "Goal/GOAL-1" } ],
        "activity": [
          { "reference": { "reference": "Task/T-RX" } },
          { "reference": { "reference": "Task/T-SCH" } },
          { "reference": { "reference": "Task/T-TRANSPORT" } },
          { "reference": { "reference": "Task/T-ATTEND" } }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}
